<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Tags/Solar on Create A Van Life</title><link>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/tags/solar/</link><description>Recent content in Tags/Solar on Create A Van Life</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en</language><copyright>© 2026 Create A Van Life</copyright><lastBuildDate>Thu, 26 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/tags/solar/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Wall vs Car vs Solar Recharge: What Matters Most</title><link>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/wall-vs-car-vs-solar-recharge-what-matters/</link><pubDate>Thu, 26 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/wall-vs-car-vs-solar-recharge-what-matters/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Use this page when you&amp;rsquo;re deciding where recovery should come from first. For most people, &lt;strong&gt;wall charging is the reliability anchor&lt;/strong&gt;, then car/drive and solar support the plan.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Trust link:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/how-we-test-and-label-claims/" &gt;How we test + how we label claims&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 class="relative group"&gt;Start here
 &lt;div id="start-here" class="anchor"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 
 &lt;span
 class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none"&gt;
 &lt;a class="text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline" href="#start-here" aria-label="Anchor"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
 &lt;/span&gt;
 
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set your baseline around wall recharge windows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Add car/drive recharge as support when driving is consistent.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Treat solar as weather-dependent margin, not your only recovery path.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;h2 class="relative group"&gt;The short answer
 &lt;div id="the-short-answer" class="anchor"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 
 &lt;span
 class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none"&gt;
 &lt;a class="text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline" href="#the-short-answer" aria-label="Anchor"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
 &lt;/span&gt;
 
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Wall recharge:&lt;/strong&gt; fastest and most repeatable recovery in most scenarios (Spec/Reported).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Car/drive recharge:&lt;/strong&gt; useful support when your weekly miles are predictable (Reported/Estimate).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Solar recharge:&lt;/strong&gt; valuable margin but variable with season, shade, and weather (Reported/Estimate).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2 class="relative group"&gt;Choose by your week, not by marketing
 &lt;div id="choose-by-your-week-not-by-marketing" class="anchor"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 
 &lt;span
 class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none"&gt;
 &lt;a class="text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline" href="#choose-by-your-week-not-by-marketing" aria-label="Anchor"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
 &lt;/span&gt;
 
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If your week is schedule-heavy or weather-noisy, prioritize the charging path that still works when conditions are average, not ideal.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Bluetti Fast Charging for Van Life: The Recovery-First Guide</title><link>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/bluetti-fast-charging/</link><pubDate>Sun, 22 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/bluetti-fast-charging/</guid><description>&lt;h1 class="relative group"&gt;Bluetti Fast Charging for Van Life: The Recovery-First Guide
 &lt;div id="bluetti-fast-charging-for-van-life-the-recovery-first-guide" class="anchor"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 
 &lt;span
 class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none"&gt;
 &lt;a class="text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline" href="#bluetti-fast-charging-for-van-life-the-recovery-first-guide" aria-label="Anchor"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
 &lt;/span&gt;
 
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In real van life, power stress usually comes from &lt;strong&gt;bad recovery&lt;/strong&gt;, not just low capacity. Heat, humidity, and cloudy stretches expose weak charging plans quickly. That’s why this page focuses on &lt;strong&gt;recovery-first decisions&lt;/strong&gt; instead of spec-sheet hype.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Hot + Cloudy Van Power Recovery: Stay Stable When Solar Drops</title><link>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/hot-and-cloudy-van-power-recovery/</link><pubDate>Sun, 22 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/hot-and-cloudy-van-power-recovery/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Hot and cloudy weeks can feel like a trap: heat pushes loads up while clouds weaken your refill.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This page is a recovery-first plan for staying stable when solar is inconsistent and comfort pressure is high.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Start here:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/heat-wave-van-power-recovery/" &gt;Heat-Wave Van Power Recovery&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/cloudy-week-power-recovery-plan/" &gt;Cloudy Week Power Recovery Plan&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2 class="relative group"&gt;The failure pattern (why drift accelerates)
 &lt;div id="the-failure-pattern-why-drift-accelerates" class="anchor"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 
 &lt;span
 class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none"&gt;
 &lt;a class="text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline" href="#the-failure-pattern-why-drift-accelerates" aria-label="Anchor"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
 &lt;/span&gt;
 
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In hot-and-cloudy weeks, drift usually accelerates for a few predictable reasons:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>How to Survive a Cloudy Week in Van Life Without Power Stress</title><link>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/cloudy-week-power-recovery-plan/</link><pubDate>Sun, 22 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/cloudy-week-power-recovery-plan/</guid><description>&lt;h1 class="relative group"&gt;How to Survive a Cloudy Week in Van Life Without Power Stress
 &lt;div id="how-to-survive-a-cloudy-week-in-van-life-without-power-stress" class="anchor"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 
 &lt;span
 class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none"&gt;
 &lt;a class="text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline" href="#how-to-survive-a-cloudy-week-in-van-life-without-power-stress" aria-label="Anchor"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
 &lt;/span&gt;
 
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A cloudy week exposes your recovery plan, not just your battery size. If refill windows shrink and daily loads stay steady, even a system that felt fine can become stressful fast. The goal is to protect stability, not chase perfect conditions.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Recovery Moves Index for Van Power: Shore, Drive, or Solar</title><link>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/recovery-moves-index/</link><pubDate>Sun, 22 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/recovery-moves-index/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Recovery works best when you choose the best move you can actually execute today.&lt;/p&gt;
