 &lt;/span&gt;
 
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Next step: use the Decision Tree to pick the next best move: &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/van-power-upgrade-decision-tree/" &gt;Van Power Upgrade Decision Tree&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.
If you are shopping, use &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/fast-charging-buyer-guides/" &gt;Fast-Charging Buyer Guides&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/fast-charging-power-station-buyer-checklist/" &gt;Fast-Charging Power Station Buyer Checklist&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;, then route to &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/best-fast-charging-power-stations/" &gt;Best Fast-Charging Power Stations&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/best-fast-charging-power-stations-under-1000/" &gt;Best Fast-Charging Power Stations Under $1000&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/best-fast-charging-power-stations-for-essentials/" &gt;Best Fast-Charging Power Stations for Essentials&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/best-fast-charging-power-stations-for-work/" &gt;Best Fast-Charging Power Stations for Work&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/best-fast-charging-power-stations-for-heat-and-humidity/" &gt;Best Fast-Charging Power Stations for Heat + Humidity&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/best-fast-charging-power-stations-for-cold-weather/" &gt;Best Fast-Charging Power Stations for Cold Weather&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.
Entry ladder and method routes: &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/best-of/power-stations-under-500/" &gt;Portable Power Stations Under $500&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/under-500-to-tier-2-upgrade-bridge/" &gt;Under-$500 to Tier 2 Upgrade Bridge&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/how-we-test-and-source-van-power/" &gt;How We Test and Source Van Power&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.
If you&amp;rsquo;re deciding between solar and fast charging, use this comparison: &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/solar-vs-fast-charging-for-van-life/" &gt;Solar vs Fast Charging for Van Life&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.
For cold weeks with weak solar, use this condition plan: &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/cold-and-cloudy-van-power-recovery/" &gt;Cold + Cloudy Van Power Recovery&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Solar Capture Window Plan: Get the Most From Solar Without Magical Thinking</title><link>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/solar-capture-window-plan/</link><pubDate>Sun, 22 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/solar-capture-window-plan/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Solar works best as a layer, not a promise.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Start here:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/cloudy-week-power-recovery-plan/" &gt;Cloudy Week Power Recovery Plan&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/parking-constraints-van-power-recovery/" &gt;Parking Constraints Van Power Recovery&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2 class="relative group"&gt;Step 1 — Plan for the “capture window” (not all-day fantasy)
 &lt;div id="step-1--plan-for-the-capture-window-not-all-day-fantasy" class="anchor"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 
 &lt;span
 class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none"&gt;
 &lt;a class="text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline" href="#step-1--plan-for-the-capture-window-not-all-day-fantasy" aria-label="Anchor"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
 &lt;/span&gt;
 
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Plan around the part of your day where parking and timing actually support harvest.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Solar Input Explained for Portable Power Stations</title><link>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/blog/solar-input-explained-for-power-stations/</link><pubDate>Sun, 22 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/blog/solar-input-explained-for-power-stations/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Solar input is useful, but it is only reliable when panel sizing, weather assumptions, and charge windows are realistic.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 class="relative group"&gt;Core Concepts
 &lt;div id="core-concepts" class="anchor"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 
 &lt;span
 class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none"&gt;
 &lt;a class="text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline" href="#core-concepts" aria-label="Anchor"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
 &lt;/span&gt;
 
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Input limits, panel voltage/current matching, and harvest variability drive outcomes more than headline panel wattage.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Solar vs Alternator Charging for Van Life: Which Builds a More Stable Power Plan?</title><link>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/solar-vs-alternator-charging/</link><pubDate>Sun, 22 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/solar-vs-alternator-charging/</guid><description>&lt;h1 class="relative group"&gt;Solar vs Alternator Charging for Van Life: Which Builds a More Stable Power Plan?
 &lt;div id="solar-vs-alternator-charging-for-van-life-which-builds-a-more-stable-power-plan" class="anchor"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 
 &lt;span
 class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none"&gt;
 &lt;a class="text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline" href="#solar-vs-alternator-charging-for-van-life-which-builds-a-more-stable-power-plan" aria-label="Anchor"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
 &lt;/span&gt;
 
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Most van power failures are &lt;strong&gt;recovery failures&lt;/strong&gt;, not storage failures. You can have enough battery on paper and still feel unstable in real weather. A stable plan is built around how reliably you can refill usable power after hard-use days.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Solar vs Fast Charging for Van Life: Which Fix Actually Stops Power Drift?</title><link>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/solar-vs-fast-charging-for-van-life/</link><pubDate>Sun, 22 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/solar-vs-fast-charging-for-van-life/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;This is about repeatable recovery, not specs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Use:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/van-battery-drift-diagnosis/" &gt;Van Battery Drift Diagnosis&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/recovery-window-priority-map/" &gt;Recovery Window Priority Map&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2 class="relative group"&gt;The real decision: what recovery window can you actually execute?
 &lt;div id="the-real-decision-what-recovery-window-can-you-actually-execute" class="anchor"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 
 &lt;span
 class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none"&gt;
 &lt;a class="text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline" href="#the-real-decision-what-recovery-window-can-you-actually-execute" aria-label="Anchor"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
 &lt;/span&gt;
 
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The practical choice is between the recovery windows you can repeat: solar capture, drive windows, shore windows, and fast charging when needed.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Van Power Planning Mistakes That Cost You Comfort (and Money)</title><link>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/van-power-planning-mistakes/</link><pubDate>Sun, 22 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/van-power-planning-mistakes/</guid><description>&lt;h1 class="relative group"&gt;Van Power Planning Mistakes That Cost You Comfort (and Money)
 &lt;div id="van-power-planning-mistakes-that-cost-you-comfort-and-money" class="anchor"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 
 &lt;span
 class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none"&gt;
 &lt;a class="text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline" href="#van-power-planning-mistakes-that-cost-you-comfort-and-money" aria-label="Anchor"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
 &lt;/span&gt;
 
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Most van power failures are &lt;strong&gt;recovery failures&lt;/strong&gt;, not battery-label failures. You can buy enough capacity on paper and still feel unstable week to week. Heat, humidity, cloud cover, and winter sun angle expose weak plans quickly.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Best Budget Solar for Van Life</title><link>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/best-of/van-solar/</link><pubDate>Sat, 21 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/best-of/van-solar/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;If you want the quick answer: most budget builders should start with a &lt;strong&gt;200W to 400W system&lt;/strong&gt; paired with a battery bank sized for one day of normal use. Oversizing too early is one of the fastest ways to blow a build budget.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Best Budget Solar Power Kits (Quick Picks)</title><link>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/gear/best-budget-solar-power-kits/</link><pubDate>Sat, 21 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/gear/best-budget-solar-power-kits/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Need the fast version? Start with a 200W modular kit and expand only after 30 days of real usage.&lt;/p&gt;
